rComments: In my year he curved so hard the average was B, but I guess he no longer curves (don't know why). Bad handwriting but organized.

Makes homework mandatory, tests and exam were designed poorly and difficulty between tests varied wildly, procrastinated on the marking, teaching style caters to students with less mathematical maturity when this is MAT157, bad and tiny handwriting that is impossible to see once you're behind the 5th row, and finally low average, but NO AJDUSTMENT.

Joe was such an amazing prof and really cared about my success. I REALLY struggled with the course and didn't take it as seriously as I should have and really thought I would fail the course, but asking Joe questions outside of class helped so much. He was very approachable and easy to talk to, making the course way less stressful.

MAT157 is certainly one of the most challenging first-year course in UofT. Even as a chemistry student I really enjoyed Joe's lectures and office hours, which make logically hard concepts really easy to understand. The course is actually graded heavily depends on term tests and final, but they are NOT unmanageable as long as you spend enough time.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Accessible outside class', 'Amazing lectures']

rComments: Amazing! Fabulous! He has his way about explaining difficult concepts easily, was always clear on proofs and derivations. The tests weren't VERY hard but required a deep understanding of the material. The TAs made the worst job marking the problem sets but that's going to change. Joe had a few moments forgetting the proof but that went okay, too.

His lectures are great and you can tell he's really knowledgable. Go to his office hours and you will find he is very good at explaining difficult concepts in a simply way and very patient with his students. Even occasionally makes a joke or two I find it adorable. The syllabus is not clear and he doesn't do a webpage or anything, but great prof.
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Graded by few things', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: A really good teacher who cares about whether you enjoy the course and understand the material
Joe is the best! Makes morning lectures endurable. Has a great sense of humour and the first prof I've had who genuinely cares about our success.

Joe is an amazing professor, and especially good for a course as challenging as MAT157. Really friendly and approachable. The tests are hard, and be prepared to spend hours on homework especially in the first few weeks. Don't give up too easily if your raw mark doesn't look too good, because he will adjust it a lot based on the difficulty.

Professor Joe Repka is the only reason that I survived UofT. He was the utmost caring and attentive professor I ever had at the school, and I was in 4 seminar courses! He really cares about his students and their grasp on the material. He wants you to do well. He is there for you extra hours. And he is highly intelligent. Thanks for everything.

Professor Repka is amazing. He is genuinely a great person and I would highly recommend his course(s) to anyone. MAT157 is lived up to its reputation as being a challenging course but Joe made it completely worth it. Also, the stories this man has are incredible so definitely attend your lectures.

Clear lectures. Carefully crafted assignments complemented and enhanced classes. Lecture style follows the textbook (just focus on understanding what he says rather than worry about writing everything down). By far the kindest professor I could have hoped for. Lots of very hard work, but he'll be there to guide you and make you love math. Have fun!
Joe is a good teacher but his writing is a little hard to read and he jumps around a lot but he is smart af and pretty much knows the material amazingly well
Very approachable and understanding. You won't regret his course.

rComments: Joe Repka is a Saint. He is a wonderful teacher, especially if you dread math. He is approachable and helpful and his classes are necessary to attend if you want to do well.

rComments: Amazing prof. My main reason for being alive after first year. Very helpful and approachable, be sure to go to his office hours if you need help.
very nice! lots of enthusiasm and help, really cares about his students doing well!

Prof Repka was the best prof I ever had! Extremely friendly and approachable! Use his office hours whenever you need help! His test and exam were exactly like the practice ones. Weekly problem sets were great way to boost average. Material content was very interesting. Overall, I give a 10/10! Best substitute to MAT135/MAT136.
Great Lecturer and amazing topics, the best course I have taken in U of T. For those who interested in biology and math, I highly recommend this course

Didn't spend nearly enough time covering the most difficult concepts/problems and spent too much time on the easier stuff. In addition, the course (esp. the calculus part of it) needs more examples specifically from biology. I was disappointed overall.
The professor makes more strictly than the TAs if you write the make-up test.
He is a good professor who first acts like he doesn't know how to solve it, and later gives us the steps.

Great prof!  Be prepared for weekly assignments but they're really easy and boost your average!  He's also very helpful in answering any questions you have, so visit him during office hours.  And all the tests are open book and there's no textbook to read so you must attend all lectures.  Overall great class!

He's a good lecturer. He's definitely knowledgeable, and a good communicator. But I wish he would have covered more advanced problems in class, and the final exam was inhumanely long. Fun course though!
WONDERFUL PROF!
Awesome prof. Very knowledgeable and clear.
he is so cute

haha! i love his teaching style, the way he goes through problems is awesome, he totally puts himself in your place and walks through it with you acting all confused and leading you to the answer. it works too i think hes a great teacher. the course was good - an excellent companion to BIO 150.
Awesome teacher.  I used to hate calculus, now I love it!
he's got to be the nicest guy.. makes calculus soo easy.. he should be teaching mat135.
very good lecturer.
Wicked class.  Covered lots of material, but he made it seem quite easy.  Be prepared for assignments, but they are quite helpful as well.
he is a breath of fresh air after calculus
I thought he taught the material well.  He always said "it looks complicated, but it really says something simple" -hilarious!
